Spring JTA Sample extracted from http://git.springsource.org/spring-samples
Updated with some changes:

 - created base class to cache the Spring context for integration tests
 - added embedded ActiveMQ broker for integration tests
 - splitted configuration of JMS and JPA into separate configuration classes
 - configured Hibernate databse schema autogeneration
 - fixed some small issues with the existing Bitronix JTA configuration
 
You need to configure a MySQL database. See the file service.properties in the 'resources' directory.
NOTE: The 'h2' Git branch uses an in-memory H2 database so you do not need to setup MySQL.
